HEADWORD: Chausses
<hw>Chausses</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<def>The garment for the legs and feet and for the body below the waist,
worn in Europe throughout the Middle Ages; applied also to the armor for
the same parts, when fixible, as of chain mail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chaussure</ent>⟦br⟧
